{"article_id":"4P2xoTnfPHxOmK93","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The White House and Congressional Republicans are squaring off in negotiations","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"to avert the fiscal cliff ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"with each side accusing the other of blocking a deal .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"For the first time we 're getting a look at what the White House is offering","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to break the stalemate .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Republicans consider it an overreach .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Democrats make clear","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"it 's a first offer ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to get specific on the numbers .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Treasury Secretary Timothy Geithner and White House Director of Legislative Affairs Rob Nabors presented the details","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"while making the rounds on Capitol Hill Thursday .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"The headlines ?","depth":3},{"id":13,"text":"The White House is asking for $ 1.6 trillion dollars in new taxes .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"This would include the president 's campaign pledge","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to raise tax rates on families","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"who make $ 250,000 a year and more .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"It would bring in additional money","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"by closing loopholes ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"limiting deductions ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"raising the estate tax rate to 2009 levels","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"and increasing capital gains and dividends taxes .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"Republican sources tell CNN","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"the $ 1.6 trillion figure is higher than any number","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"the White House had previously presented","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and was so disarming ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"according to one source ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"it set the talks back .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Democrats say","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"the GOP is feigning outrage .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"In September 2011 , Obama first proposed raising taxes one and a half trillion dollars","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"- at that time","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"to pay for the so-called Jobs Bill .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Republicans dismissed it as a political stunt with no chance of movement .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"It would seem the White House is digging in on its position on taxes","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"- or at least making their stance clearer to the Republicans and the public .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Reflecting a new aggressive posture by the Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"the proposal","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"laid out by Geithner","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"also called for additional spending ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"including $ 50 billion in new stimulus spending next year , a home mortgage refinancing plan , an extension of unemployment insurance and an extension of the payroll tax cut .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"It includes a permanent mechanism","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"to vote on a debt limit increase ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"which would avoid the kind of crisis","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"the U.S. faced in the summer of 2011 .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"In return ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"according to multiple sources ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"the Obama administration is offering to find $ 400 billion in new cuts to Medicare and other entitlement programs ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"with the specifics","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"to be hammered out next year .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"While Republicans called these proposals unbalanced and unreasonable ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"White House aides made clear","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"the president is ready to take a counter offer .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"This all amounts to an elaborate negotiating dance .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"With time running out","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"until tax rates automatically rise","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"and drastic spending cuts kick in","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"- part of the so-called sequester -","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"both sides are playing for leverage against the clock .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Democrats are emboldened by electoral successes and that the president won a second term","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"while pledging to do what the Republicans are still objecting to :","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"raise tax rates for the wealthiest .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Democrats believe","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"the Republicans must and will relent on that point .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"To that end ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"CNN learned","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"in a phone call Wednesday night","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"Obama told Boehner","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"there would be no deal","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"unless the GOP agrees to raise tax rates for the wealthiest .","depth":16},{"id":70,"text":"That means recently floated alternatives","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"- including closing loopholes or limiting deductions -","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"would not be enough on their own .","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"Rates must go up as well for the top 2 % of income earners .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Republicans tried to turn the conversation away from taxes ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"insisting","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"the real debate should be about spending cuts .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"`` Despite claims","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"that the president supports a balanced approach ,","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"Democrats have yet to get serious about real spending cuts , ''","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Boehner told reporters Thursday .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Reflecting a growing sense of pessimism among Republicans ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"the speaker added ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"`` no substantive progress has been made in the talks between the White House and the House over the lat two weeks . ''","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"In a statement","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"that accused Republicans of blocking a deal","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"to protect `` the very wealthiest individuals , ''","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"White House Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest responded to the GOP in an email .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"`` The President has already signed into law over $ 1 trillion in spending cuts","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"and we remain willing to do tough things","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"to compromise ,","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"and it 's time","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"for Republicans in Washington to join the chorus of other voices","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"- from the business community to the middle class Americans across the country -","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"who support a balanced approach","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"that asks more from the wealthiest Americans , ''","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"Earnest said .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":193,"left":0,"right":192,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":192,"left":107,"right":191,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":99,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":104,"right":105,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":100,"right":103,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":6,"right":102,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":7,